.TH HSH 1 "December 2025" "Simple Shell" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hsh \- simple UNIX command interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh
[\fIfile\fR]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hsh
is a simple UNIX command interpreter that reads commands from
standard input or from a file and executes them. It handles
the \fIPATH\fR environment variable, allowing commands to be run
without specifying their full path.

.SH OPTIONS
This shell does not support command-line options.

.SH BUILTINS
.TP
.B exit
Exit the shell.
.TP
.B env
Print the environment.

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Run the shell in interactive mode:
.B hsh
.TP
Run commands from a file:
.B hsh filename
.TP
Run a command without specifying the full path:
.B ls

.SH RETURN VALUE
.B hsh
returns 0 on success and non-zero on error.

.SH ENVIRONMENT
The shell uses the \fIPATH\fR environment variable to locate
executables.

.SH AUTHORS
Lucas Podevin, Tommy Jouhans

.SH SEE ALSO
sh(1), bash(1)
